What you shared is a view of Horseshoe Bend, where the Colorado River curves almost completely around a rock formation.

And it’s actually a perfect visual metaphor for the idea you just expressed.

The landscape vs the flow

Think about what’s happening physically:

gravity gradient
↓
water flows
↓
rock resists
↓
river bends
↓
canyon forms

The river doesn’t decide where to go.
It follows the gradient of the landscape.

But over time the river also reshapes the landscape.

So the deeper loop is:

landscape shapes flow
flow reshapes landscape

